fields.name: layers
fields.description: The layers where the configuration should be applied

bits.name: ram
bits.description: Update configuration in the RAM layer

bits.name: bbr
bits.description: Update configuration in the BBR layer

bits.name: flash
bits.description: Update configuration in the Flash layer

bits.name: action
bits.description: Transaction action to be applied: 0 = Transactionless UBX-CFG-VALSET: In the next UBX-CFG-VALSET, it can be either 0 or 1. If a transaction has not yet been started, the incoming configuration is applied (if valid). If a transaction has already been started, cancels any started transaction and the incoming configuration is applied (if valid). 1 = (Re)Start set transaction: In the next UBX-CFG-VALSET, it can be either 0, 1, 2 or 3. If a transaction has not yet been started, a transaction will be started. If a transaction has already been started, restarts the transaction, effectively removing all previous non-applied UBX-CFG-VALSET messages. 2 = Set transaction ongoing: In the next UBX-CFG-VALSET, it can be either 0, 1, 2 or 3. 3 = Apply and end a set transaction: In the next UBX-CFG-VALSET, it can be either 0 or 1.

fields.name: layer
fields.description: The layer from which the configuration item was retrieved: 0 - RAM layer, 1 - BBR, 2 - Flash, 7 - Default

fields.name: position
fields.description: Number of configuration items skipped in the result set before constructing this message (mirrors the equivalent field in the request message)

fields.name: cfgData
fields.description: Configuration data (key and value pairs). Each item is a U4 keyId followed by a value of variable size depending on the keyId. This field fills the remaining payload.

bits.description: Update configuration in the BBR layer

bits.name: flash

bits.name: reserved
bits.description: Reserved bits

fields.name: flags
fields.description: Transaction control flags. Bits 0-1 define the action.

bits.name: action
bits.description: Transaction action: 0 = Transactionless UBX-CFG-VALSET (apply immediately, cancels existing transactions); 1 = (Re)Start set transaction (start new transaction or restart existing); 2 = Set transaction ongoing (continue existing transaction); 3 = Apply and end a set transaction.
